  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Several locations in Tennessee can be suitable for hosting a prom, offering various amenities and atmospheres. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Union Station Hotel, Nashville** - This historic venue offers elegant ballrooms and beautiful architecture, ideal for a sophisticated prom night.\n\n2. **Loveless Barn, Nashville** - Known for its rustic charm, this barn venue can provide a unique and intimate atmosphere for a prom.\n\n3. **Chattanooga Choo Choo, Chattanooga** - This classic venue offers spacious areas and a touch of historic flair, perfect for a memorable event.\n\n4. **The Barn at Sycamore Farms, Arrington** - With beautiful outdoor spaces and a picturesque barn, this venue is great for a prom with a country vibe.\n\n5. **The Factory at Franklin, Franklin** - This eclectic venue offers plenty of space and a distinctive industrial charm, making it suitable for large gatherings.\n\n6. **Crowne Plaza Knoxville Downtown University, Knoxville** - This hotel venue provides elegant ballrooms and a convenient location in downtown Knoxville.\n\n7. **The Pavilion at Hunter Valley Farm, Knoxville** - Offering both indoor and outdoor spaces, this venue combines natural beauty with stylish facilities.\n\n8. **The Carriage House, Jackson** - A classic Southern venue with lush gardens and a charming interior, ideal for a romantic prom night.\n\n9. **Memphis Botanic Garden, Memphis** - This venue offers beautiful gardens and spacious areas for a picturesque prom setting.\n\n10. **Mansion at Fontanel, Nashville** - A luxurious venue with grand surroundings and expansive ballrooms, perfect for a glamorous prom event.\n\nThese venues offer a variety of styles and settings to accommodate different themes and sizes of prom events.",
